postcontent:
Folks, this is free information.  Don't get scammed by these people wanting stupid money for .22 rounds.  Prices for .22 rounds should range from the low end of .05 cent each, to the high end competition rounds for .25 each.  You can buy 1000 rounds of CCI Mini Mag 40 grain 1260 ft per second copper jacketed for $80 with shipping to your door.  These fools wanting $85 for 525 rounds of low grade range ammo are insane.  I'm sure those gouging the public will flag this quickly, but if even one person who is thinking about buying reads this and saves their money, then it accomplished the goal.  Academy Sports has ammo come in 3 times a week, and here recently it's been lasting far longer than the 20 minutes it used to disappear in.  Even .223 has become easier to get.  Save your money!

Edit 4/29  Love the hate mail from you gougers.  It proves what a bunch of Aholes you all are.  Those asking where to buy, Walmart and Academy Sports are getting ammo 2-3 times  a week.  Online vendors like PalmettoStateArmory.com get it a couple times as well.  Sign up for email stock alerts and you can get realistically priced .22 ammo.

postcontent:
Up for sale is my S&W M&P9c chambered in 9mm. It is in perfect condition. I have found the compact model to be more accurate than the full size, but that's just my experience. It can nail the bullseye at 10 yards easily. I bought it January 4th from a dealer in Waukesha right when the "ban" craze started, so it took me a very long time to hunt one down.
